
Passy, 20 May 1778. printed: JA, Diary and Autobiography, 4:104. In his reply to Fleurys letter of 26 April (above), Adams noted the excellent reputation of Franois Louis Teissdre de Fleury, then serving with the Continental Army, and congratulated Fleury and his wife upon the honor of having such a Son. He then stated, to remove any uneasiness, that the younger Fleurys Pay and Appointments should be adequate for his subsistence.
